WEBVTT

01:58.690 --> 02:22.322
food but sometimes you need a fast regarding certain things that you're doing it might be taking your attention away and I'm not really going to go into that aspect of my message today regarding the fasting part but just what he had to say about the importance of prayer I thought was really really a good thing so going back to my original statement you know I've struggled to procrastination and trying to overcome that

02:23.330 --> 02:32.419
And I'm being intentional about doing a little bit every day to make sure that I'm not putting things off that I typically would put off.

02:33.000 --> 02:35.222
So it makes things a little bit less stressful for sure.

02:35.262 --> 02:47.254
So I thought that the importance of prayer would be a good way to follow up with that message because prayer is needed to help in your struggles of things you're dealing with that you're trying to overcome.

02:49.477 --> 02:50.738
So fun facts.

02:51.170 --> 02:55.895
The word prayer is mentioned in the Bible 850 times.

02:57.337 --> 02:58.458
You may not have been aware of that.

02:59.940 --> 03:11.152
And in the Bible, there's over 650 prayers listed in the Bible and approximately 450 recorded answers to prayer in the Bible.

03:15.077 --> 03:16.138
So I have a question for you.

03:16.158 --> 03:19.762
I have a audience participation.

03:20.610 --> 03:23.593
When is the first time prayers mentioned in the Bible?

03:24.354 --> 03:25.295
Anybody have any idea?

03:30.061 --> 03:30.441
Anyone.

03:32.083 --> 03:32.383
All right.

03:32.403 --> 03:33.925
Well, I'll go ahead and let you know when it is.

03:34.245 --> 03:36.848
So we're going to go to Genesis 4, verse 26.

03:40.232 --> 03:44.036
And Adam knew his wife again, and she bore a son and named him Seth.

03:44.557 --> 03:49.362
For God has appointed another seed for me instead of Abel, whom Cain killed.

03:49.730 --> 04:02.186
And as far and as for Seth to him, also a son was born and he named him Enosh, then men began to call on the name of the Lord.

04:02.406 --> 04:08.814
So that's what first mentions that man started to have a relationship with God or seeking after him.

04:10.115 --> 04:13.159
So God desires to have a close relationship with us.

04:15.983 --> 04:18.546
This cannot be accomplished.

04:19.682 --> 04:23.846
If we're not in communion with him, we have to make sure we're in communion of God.

04:25.968 --> 04:31.553
The more we communicate with others, the stronger our relationships become with each other.

04:32.374 --> 04:34.476
This is true in our prayer life as well.

04:36.638 --> 04:48.690
When I shared with Kim what my message was going to be about, she mentioned a study that she'd heard about where they did brain scans of people having conversations with each other.

04:49.090 --> 04:53.674
And certain parts of your brain will light up when you're having a conversation with somebody.

04:54.375 --> 04:57.818
They also did scans of people's brains when they're praying.

04:57.858 --> 05:02.823
Those same parts of your brain light up when you're communicating with God.

05:04.004 --> 05:13.813
So the study concluded that your body knows you're communicating with an outside being and not just having your words going out into nothingness.

05:14.574 --> 05:18.898
This is proof that a relationship is being developed

05:19.522 --> 05:21.644
when we are praying to our Father.

05:21.985 --> 05:24.087
We're having conversation with Him.

05:25.708 --> 05:26.890
And our bodies know that.

05:28.812 --> 05:38.762
Let's look at an example that Jesus shared with His example, excuse me, let's look at an example of Jesus shared with His disciples of how we should pray.

05:38.782 --> 05:43.186
So we're gonna go to Matthew six, verses five through 14.

05:43.206 --> 05:46.770
And when you pray,

05:48.322 --> 06:15.730
do not be like the hypocrites for they love to pray standing in the synagogues and on the street corners to be seen by others truly I tell you they have received the reward in full but when you pray goes to your room close the door and pray to your father who is unseen then your father who sees what is done in secret will reward you and when you pray do not keep on babbling like pagans for they

06:16.194 --> 06:18.797
They think they'll be heard because of their many words.

06:19.517 --> 06:22.981
Do not be like them for your father knows what you need before you ask him.

06:23.061 --> 06:25.523
So he already knows what you're needing before you ask.

06:28.266 --> 06:30.068
This then is how you should pray.

06:30.128 --> 06:34.773
Our father in heaven, hallowed be your name, your kingdom come.

06:35.714 --> 06:39.538
Your will be done on earth as it is in heaven.

06:40.519 --> 06:43.762
Give us today our daily bread and forgive us our debts.

06:44.290 --> 06:59.813
as we also forgive our debtors and lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from the evil one for if you forgive other people when you sin against your heavenly father, your heavenly father will forgive us as well.

07:01.676 --> 07:05.742
This is the way we should pray commonly called the Lord's Prayer.

07:07.104 --> 07:13.554
This is the model Jesus shared for all prayer, emphasizing

07:13.890 --> 07:18.036
worship God's kingdom, provision and forgiveness.

07:19.397 --> 07:25.385
We need to be intentional about taking prayer seriously and not have it be a vain repetition.

07:26.887 --> 07:37.121
It's easy for us to get stuck in a rut and just go through the motions and pray to God like we're making a laundry list or our list for our groceries that we're getting.

07:38.283 --> 07:43.890
So here's an example also of how to pray and how not to pray.

07:44.706 --> 07:48.690
So we're going to go to Luke 18 verses nine through 14.

07:48.910 --> 07:54.576
It's a parable of the Pharisee and the tax collector.

07:55.857 --> 08:01.742
Also, he spoke this parable to some who trusted in themselves that they were righteous and despised others.

08:02.203 --> 08:06.467
Two men went up to the temple to pray, one a Pharisee, the other tax collector.

08:07.448 --> 08:13.714
The Pharisee stood and prayed thus with himself, God, I thank you that I'm not like other men, extortioners,

08:13.922 --> 08:16.945
unjust, adulterers, or even as this tax collector.

08:17.546 --> 08:18.587
I fast twice a week.

08:18.887 --> 08:20.890
I give tithes of all that I possess.

08:21.590 --> 08:28.158
And the tax collector standing afar off would not as much as race as eyes to heaven, standing afar off.

08:30.020 --> 08:33.143
But beat his breasts, saying God be merciful to me as sinner.

08:33.503 --> 08:37.368
I tell you, this man went down to his house justified rather than the other.

08:38.228 --> 08:43.314
Everyone who exalts himself and who humbles himself will be exalted.

08:44.898 --> 08:54.271
It's all about being humble before the Lord, knowing we cannot do this on our own.

08:54.331 --> 08:56.314
We need to have His help.

08:56.454 --> 08:59.919
We need to pray for help and guidance on everything.

09:02.162 --> 09:09.252
It's about being raw, sharing with Him everything because life is messy.

09:09.453 --> 09:10.354
It just is.

09:13.506 --> 09:21.259
We need to share our deepest concerns, our wounding, our successes, our failures, our disappointments.

09:22.701 --> 09:30.354
He is our loving Father who loves us so very much and knows all of our weaknesses and frailties, and he wants to help us.

09:32.297 --> 09:34.280
He is with us through everything we go through.

09:35.162 --> 09:40.050
Jesus set the example of praying often and for everything.

09:41.346 --> 09:46.674
So over this past weekend, when we had the snowstorm come through, we had to cancel services because of it.

09:49.799 --> 09:54.887
It got me thinking about how dependent we really are on God's love and provision for us.

09:56.289 --> 09:57.591
So we live in a modern world.

09:57.631 --> 10:02.919
We can go to the grocery store, you know, 24 seven, well, pre-COVID.

10:05.162 --> 10:07.506
And we can pretty much buy anything we want.

10:09.314 --> 10:15.764
We can fill our refrigerators up with food and we can have everything there without having to go hunt for our next meal.

10:15.844 --> 10:19.690
So we have modern day conveniences of being able to go and get food.

10:19.751 --> 10:22.174
And it's easy for us to take these things for granted.

10:25.179 --> 10:34.514
So like a lot of people, we decided to go to the store a few days before the snowstorm was coming to make sure we had the provisions that we needed before the storm.

10:35.458 --> 10:38.201
And because we didn't know what was going to happen, you know, the power might go out.

10:38.261 --> 10:49.912
We had no idea because they're talking about 18 inches of snow and thankfully we were within the zone where it's just snow and not ice, a lot of areas as we know where power was out and such.

10:51.173 --> 10:55.377
So I went to the store also the day before the storm to get a few things.

10:55.437 --> 10:57.679
And I noticed like the shelves are bare.

10:58.861 --> 11:02.084
Bread was gone, milk, eggs, all the essentials gone.

11:02.484 --> 11:04.466
So it's easy to take these things for granted.

11:04.610 --> 11:06.693
We also bought a generator a few years ago.

11:07.614 --> 11:15.584
Um, brand new, haven't touched it, haven't prepared it as like, well, it's maybe sometime during the summer, I'll get this thing going to make sure it works.

11:15.684 --> 11:16.625
Well, didn't do that.

11:17.105 --> 11:23.213
So scrambling around before the storm, just in case the power is going to go down, I thought I should at least have it ready.

11:23.794 --> 11:30.242
So I willed it into the garage and, um, still didn't like get it set up, but we went and got some gas.

11:31.103 --> 11:33.746
Uh, went and got a five gallon container.

11:34.018 --> 11:35.400
for gas, Kim went and bought one.

11:36.602 --> 11:39.046
And we thought, we better fill that up just in case.

11:40.027 --> 11:44.915
And then Kim mentioned, she's like, what if the gas stations ran out of gas?

11:44.975 --> 11:49.643
I mean, it's a possibility, because they tell everybody, make sure to fill up your tanks on your car.

11:49.743 --> 11:52.267
So you've got gas in case you get stuck on the storm.

11:52.768 --> 11:57.896
At least you'll have gas in your car to keep you warm if you're stuck and such.

11:58.837 --> 12:02.002
So these are kind of things to think about, because it's easy.

12:02.530 --> 12:07.475
to not decently be prepared ahead of time, but the last minute, oh, we better get all prepared for this.

12:09.638 --> 12:13.301
So thankfully, as you know, the power did not go out, which was nice.

12:14.162 --> 12:24.113
But it got me to thinking about the parable of the 10 virgins and how five were prepared, but five were not.

12:25.715 --> 12:28.978
So let's go to Matthew 25,

12:30.594 --> 12:34.218
turn with me to there as well, and we will go through this parable.

12:36.040 --> 12:39.884
Then the kingdom of heaven shall be likened to 10 virgins who took their lamps.

12:40.224 --> 12:41.746
They went out to meet the bridegroom.

12:42.347 --> 12:45.230
Now five of them were wise and five were foolish.

12:46.231 --> 12:53.378
Those who were foolish took their lamps and they took no oil with them, but the wise took oil in their vessels with their lamps.

12:53.398 --> 12:56.201
But while the bridegroom delayed, they slumbered and slept.

12:57.703 --> 13:00.466
And at midnight, a cry was heard, behold,

13:00.770 --> 13:07.199
the bridegroom is coming, go out to meet him, then all those virgins arose and trimmed their lamps.

13:07.900 --> 13:11.825
And the foolish said to the wise, give us some of your oil for our lamps are going out.

13:12.366 --> 13:19.415
But the wise answered saying, no, less there should not be enough for us and you, but go rather to those who sell and buy for yourselves.

13:19.856 --> 13:27.346
And while they went to buy, the bridegroom came and those who were ready went in with him to the wedding and the door was shut.

13:28.802 --> 13:32.526
Afterward, the other versions came also saying, Lord, Lord, open to us.

13:32.686 --> 13:36.950
But he answered and said assuredly, I say, I don't know you.

13:39.193 --> 13:44.618
Watch therefore for you know, neither the day nor the hour in which the Son of man is coming.

13:44.659 --> 13:49.624
So we're told to watch and be prepared for Christ's return.

13:51.285 --> 13:55.730
And praying is a first step in developing a close relationship with our father.

13:57.058 --> 14:00.342
This is how we develop a relationship with God the Father and Jesus.

14:01.944 --> 14:10.675
We do not want to be the five unprepared virgins that are told assuredly, I say, I do not know you.

14:12.076 --> 14:15.941
As I mentioned before, God is wanting a close relationship with us.

14:17.403 --> 14:19.245
He loves and wants to help us.

14:21.268 --> 14:26.514
So let's go to Matthew six, verses 25 through 34.

14:26.978 --> 14:28.119
to talk about this some more.

14:32.063 --> 14:42.553
Therefore I say to you, do not worry about your life, what you will eat, what you will drink, know what your body, nor about your body, what you will put on.

14:43.354 --> 14:47.758
It's not life more than food and the body more than clothing.

14:48.219 --> 14:55.826
Look at the birds of the air, for they neither sow nor reap nor gather into barns yet your father

14:56.546 --> 14:58.248
your Heavenly Father feeds them.

14:58.269 --> 15:00.932
Are you not more valuable than they?

15:00.972 --> 15:06.060
Which of you by worrying can add one qubit to your stature.

15:08.463 --> 15:10.186
So why do you worry about clothing?

15:10.406 --> 15:12.590
Consider the lilies of the field, how they grow.

15:12.630 --> 15:14.072
They neither toil nor spin.

15:14.112 --> 15:21.062
And yet I say to you that even Solomon in all of his glory was not arrayed like one of these.

15:21.643 --> 15:23.826
Now, if God cleaves the grass of the field,

15:24.418 --> 15:30.467
which today is, and tomorrow is thrown into the oven, will he not much more clothe you of little faith.

15:31.268 --> 15:35.034
Therefore, do not worry saying, what shall I eat?

15:35.394 --> 15:36.195
What shall I drink?

15:36.576 --> 15:37.337
What shall I wear?

15:37.938 --> 15:51.698
For after all these things, a Gentile seek for your heavenly father knows that you need all these things, but seek first the kingdom of God and his righteousness and all these things shall be added to you.

15:52.514 --> 15:54.716
Therefore, do not worry about tomorrow for tomorrow.

15:54.896 --> 15:56.758
We'll worry about its own things.

15:58.820 --> 16:02.084
Sufficient for the day is its own trouble.

16:03.605 --> 16:12.935
You know, we still need to make sure that we're good providers for our families and being prepared each day.

16:12.975 --> 16:19.922
And the way to do this is to put God first foremost by having our armor on.

16:21.058 --> 16:27.646
The point here is not to worry and to be in constant state of fear, but rather putting our trust in God.

16:30.449 --> 16:45.288
There are many examples of prayer in the Bible, prayers of faith, prayers of agreement, prayers of petition, prayers of Thanksgiving, prayers of worship, prayers of consecration, prayers of intercession and praying in the spirit.

16:46.910 --> 16:50.514
So today I just wanted to do an overview about just the importance of prayer.

16:50.786 --> 16:55.115
and how we need to have it in our lives and how we need to have a close relationship with God.

16:56.718 --> 17:05.296
Perhaps the next time, if I feel like I'm led to do so, we can go deeper into the different aspects of prayer of all these different areas.

17:06.197 --> 17:10.386
But in the meantime, don't forget about the importance of prayer.

